item.title: Noclip issue 317
item.dc:creator: @runescape_sucks runescape sucks
item.description:
@runescape_sucks wrote:

That is not at all how ‘voids’ work.
If it was a void, which I don’t believe it should be, it would probably be as so (just for your reference)

public void noclip() { //blah code }

This is what it would probably look like in the client, where it belongs. (from what I can tell you tried to put this in the server.)

In client.java

[code=java] if (inputString.equals("::noclip")) {
for (int k1 = 0; k1 < 4; k1++) {
for (int i2 = 1; i2 < 103; i2++) {
for (int k2 = 1; k2 < 103; k2++)
aClass11Array1230[k1].anIntArrayArray294[i2][k2] = 0;

							}
						}
					}[/code]

If you can’t find it, try searching for ‘::’ in your client.java.
